## Get Mentions
def get_menions(line):
    words = re.findall("(^|[^@\w])@(\w{1,15})", line)
    words = [word[1] for word in words]

    return words

tweets_df['mentions'] = tweets_df['text'].progress_apply(get_menions)

## Sentiment Analysis
def get_tweet_sentiment(tweet): 
    '''
    Utility function to classify sentiment of passed tweet
    using textblob's sentiment method
    '''
    # create TextBlob object of passed tweet text
    tweet = ' '.join(re.sub(r"(@[A-Za-z0-9]+)|([^0-9A-Za-z \t])|(\w+:\/\/\S+)", " ", tweet).split())
    analysis = TextBlob(tweet)
    # set sentiment
    if analysis.sentiment.polarity > 0:
        return 'positive'
    elif analysis.sentiment.polarity == 0:
        return 'neutral'
    else:
        return 'negative'

tweets_df['sentiment'] = tweets_df['text'].progress_apply(get_tweet_sentiment)
tweets_df['sentiment'].value_counts()

from IPython.core.display import HTML

def get_html(_row):
    username = _row['username']
    screen_name = _row['screen_name']
    date = _row['timestamp'].strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')
    likes = _row['likes']
    replies = _row['replies']
    retweets = _row['retweets']
    text = _row['text_html']
    head = f'<p><strong>{username}</strong> </p><p> {screen_name} -----  Tweeted on: {date} \n</p>'
    tail = (
        f'<p>\n<strong>Likes</strong>: {likes}\t <strong>Replies</strong>: {replies}\t <strong>Retweets</strong>: {retweets}\n\n\n</p>' +
        '<p>_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________</p>'
    )
    html = head + text + tail
    return html
